        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(outbound): strip inbound metadata before delivery",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFixes #39847. Related to #41355, #30405, #28170.\n\nWhen an LLM echoes internal metadata blocks (e.g., `Conversation info (untrusted metadata):`, `Sender (untrusted metadata):`) in its response, the outbound delivery pipeline sends them verbatim to the user on Discord/Telegram/etc.\n\n`stripInboundMetadata()` already exists and is used in:\n- TUI display (`chat-sanitize.ts`)\n- Session cost calculations (`session-cost-usage.ts`)\n\nBut it was never called in the delivery pipeline (`normalizeReplyPayloadsForDelivery`).\n\n## Changes\n\n- `src/infra/outbound/payloads.ts` — import and call `stripInboundMetadata()` on payload text before parsing reply directives\n- `src/infra/outbound/payloads.test.ts` — add test verifying metadata blocks are stripped before delivery\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [x] Added test: payload with echoed metadata block → metadata stripped, actual response preserved\n- [x] All 9 tests in `payloads.test.ts` pass\n- [x] `pnpm build && pnpm check` — clean\n\n> AI-assisted: test case co-authored with Claude (Anthropic).",
